description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c line 362-374

The protobuf spec (https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/encoding/) limits field numbers to 1-536870911 (2^29 - 1). The `pb_read_key` function in adapter.c only rejects field numbers > UINT32_MAX:

```c
if (ret < 0 || (key >> 3) == 0U || (key >> 3) > UINT32_MAX) {
    return -EINVAL;
}
```

This allows field numbers 536870912-4294967295, which violate the protobuf spec.

In contrast, codec.c correctly validates against PB_MAX_FIELD_NUMBER (536870911ULL):
```c
if (field64 == 0U || field64 > PB_MAX_FIELD_NUMBER) {
    return -EINVAL;
}
```

Impact: Messages with invalid field numbers are accepted instead of rejected. While these invalid fields would be skipped by the switch statements and handled by pb_skip_value, this is a spec violation that could cause interoperability issues with strict parsers.

Fix: Add the PB_MAX_FIELD_NUMBER constant to adapter.c and use it in pb_read_key, matching codec.c's implementation.
